Sentencas: In fuel cell electrodes where the thin, active electrode layer is supported by a porous layer the diffusion processes as well as the change in the gas phase composition due to the conversion of reactants in the electrode reaction will influence the cell impedance.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Two models are developed for the description of these processes.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The first is a CSTR (continuously stirred tank reactor) model based on a well convected gas supply volume equipped with gas inlet and outlet.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Since the current distribution on the electrode surface is uniform, the impedance is derived for perturbation from a steady state and contributions from kinetics are directly additive.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the other model the gas supply is considered as a plug, flow along the electrode surface.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is assumed that the gas flow channel is sufficiently thin to eliminate any concentration gradients perpendicular to the flow direction.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this case the current density decreases in the flow direction due to consumption of reactants and accumulation of products.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For simplicity this model is restricted to cases dominated by mass transfer and conversion of the gas supplied.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Qualitatively the predictions of the two models are alike.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At high frequencies a Warburg diffusion impedance is seen.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Depending on the dimensions of the gas volume relative to the supporting layer this may turn towards the real axis as a nernstian diffusion impedance, or directly into the semicircle dominating the low frequency region.
Titulo: Diffusion and conversion impedance in solid oxide fuel cells
